  "body": "Hello, I am benchmarking the local Optimism docker image. By going to `optimism/ops` and then running `docker compose up`.\r\n\r\nTo complete my benchmark, I have to know the exact blocktime and configs used in the ethereum and optimism node running. \r\n\r\nThe way I understand it, ethereum in hardhat is running POA clique consensus algo. What I need is the following information `period` and `epoch`, normally specified in the `genesis { config }`  genesis.json\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"config\": {\r\n        \"chainId\": <yourChainId>,\r\n        \"homesteadBlock\": 0,\r\n        \"eip150Block\": 0,\r\n        \"eip155Block\": 0,\r\n        \"eip158Block\": 0,\r\n        \"byzantiumBlock\": 0,\r\n        \"clique\": {\r\n            \"period\": <yourPeriodInSecs>,\r\n            \"epoch\": <yourEpochInBlocks>\r\n        }\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nAny help would be highly appreciated.\r\n\r\n",
